Insights 1.0¶

Top 5 cities being used for analysing number of product shipped.¶

Out[113]:
array(['narsinghpura', 'mehsana', 'bangalore', 'chennai', 'ahmedabad',
       'chennai - south'], dtype=object)

1. Cities that order most number of products.¶

  1. Narsinghpura the most, it also saw a peak between 8-15th of both the months. Need more months data to validate this further though.
  2. Most top cities got shipped less than 7.5k products on each day, except Narsinghpura which stayed in the 7.5k-20k bracket and mostly in 7.5-15k bracket.

2. Plant shipping number of products on a given date.¶

  1. K shipped more products through out two months. 7.5K to 25k products a day and sometime even 30k a day.
  2. C stayed mostly in the 7.5-15k range with sometimes as low as 2.5k products a day.

3. Similary for SKUs¶

  1. Original equipments were shipped more. 10k-30 and sometime 35k a day.
  2. Whereas Replacement equipment from 2.5k to 15k a day.

O stands for OEM (Original Equipment Manufacturer) while R stands for Replacement market.

4. City wise, product distribution:¶

  1. Narsinghpura ordered close to 95k X40, 90k X48 and so on.
  2. Similarly for other cities graphs are shown.

5. Similary, From plant and Business (number of different products shipped)¶

  1. K shipped out more than 200k X85, 175k X40 and so on.
  2. Original equipment: X40 - 175k times and so on. Replacement: X85 - More than 500k

6. Top 5 products' total demand increase or decrease with time.¶

  1. X85 stays in most demand and demand peaks once or twice a week more than usual. Need more data to validate though.

Future:¶

  1. With more data, we can use time series forecasting techniques, predict different product demands and truck types needed make the shipments.
  2. As Vehicle numbers are given by RTOs in an ascending manner, we can find out how new a particular truck is and hence find out which engine type it has for instance BS5 or BS6 in recently.
  3. With real time data on where a particular truck is we can provide insights on how to arrange trucks for a particular shipment in least time and cost.
